commit.message: Update README to start with easiest example and mention HTML-drawing.
Refactor `_write_html()` and `Context` to be more focused.
Standardize available parameters.
Use named colours where possible.
Remove __main__ script.
Rename gmplot.py to google_map_plotter.py.
Refactor `scatter()` to have it use kwargs.
Refactor `marker()` drawing and have it use kwargs.
Refactor `geocode()` to have it use kwargs.
Refactor `from_geocode()` to have it use all available map kwargs.
Refactor map drawing and have it use kwargs.

Refactor `grid()` drawing and have it use kwargs.

This also fixes it so that multiple grids can be drawn on the same map.
Make `geocode()` a static method.

Make circles non-clickable.

This would allow clicking on top of a circle to place a marker, if `enable_marker_dropping()` is set.
Formally add precision argument to interfaces that don't have it.
Refactor circle and symbol drawing and have them use kwargs.
Refactor `polyline()` drawing and have it use kwargs.
Refactor `polygon()` drawing and have it use kwargs.
Improve legibility of some elements' draw code.
Draw various map elements as generic drawable items.
Refactor `heatmap()` drawing and have it use kwargs.
Refactor `ground_overlay()` drawing and have it use kwargs.
Remove unused variables and functions.
Make Google Maps template strings non-public.
Make `Symbol` non-public.
Rename all mentions of 'long' to 'lng'.
Pull drawable classes out of gmplot.py.
Replace Makefile with invoke's tasks.py.
Update version to 1.4.1.
